stories.title: South Africa shrug off drug scandal to win sixth one-dayer by 53 runs
stories.summary:
South Africa's cricketers put the controversy of the past 24 hours behind
them with a courageous 53-run win in the sixth one-day international at the
Queen's Park Oval, dismissing the home side for 137 after they themselves
were bundled out for 190
